<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 26 at 7:48AM EDT  by NWS Pittsburgh</headline>
<description>...AN AREA OF SNOW SHOWERS WILL AFFECT SOUTHEASTERN
BEAVER...SOUTHERN BUTLER...NORTHERN ALLEGHENY AND NORTHWESTERN
WESTMORELAND COUNTIES...
At 746 AM EDT, an area of snow showers was located over Wexford, or
over McCandless Township, moving east at 30 mph.
Locations impacted include...
Ross Township, McCandless Township, Cranberry, Moon Township, Butler,
Franklin Park, Aliquippa, Monaca, Shaler Township, Plum, Hampton
Township, and Robinson Township.
This includes the following highways...
Pennsylvania Turnpike between mile markers 24 and 49.
Interstate 79 in Pennsylvania between mile markers 64 and 83.
Interstate 376 in Pennsylvania between mile markers 45 and 57.
Visibilities will drop quickly to less than one of a mile with a
quick half inch to inch of accumulation from this shower.</description>
